TO LESBIA (LI.)

HIM rival to the gods I place, Him loftier yet, if loftier be,

who, Lesbia, sits before thy face, Who listens and who looks on thee ;

Thee, smiling soft. Yet this delight 5 Doth all my sense consign to death;
